WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:15.288
Here's the mistake that quietly wipes out new traders.
They find something that worked beautifully on past data,
bet real money on it, and watch it fall apart. This little
row of tabs is exactly how you avoid that.

2
00:00:15.888 --> 00:00:28.920
Start with In-Sample. This is your laboratory. It's the
original window of trades you used to find your edge, to
tune your target, your stop, and your setup. Everything
you discovered here, you discovered by staring at this
exact data.

3
00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:43.464
And that is precisely the danger. It's easy to find a rule
that looks flawless on data you have already seen. Traders
call that overfitting. You've basically memorized the
answers to a test you already took. The real question is
whether it works on data you have never touched.

4
00:00:44.064 --> 00:00:59.304
That is exactly what Out-of-Sample is for. These are later
windows of trades your edge never saw. You take the same
rule from your lab, apply it here untouched, and see if it
still holds up. You get three independent out-of-sample
windows, so you can check it across different market
conditions.

5
00:00:59.904 --> 00:01:14.064
And the Compare tab puts them side by side. In-sample
versus out-of-sample, with the difference in strike rate
and expected value laid right out. If the numbers hold,
your edge is probably real. If they collapse out of
sample, you fooled yourself in the lab.

6
00:01:14.664 --> 00:01:29.376
One Study is one complete experiment, with its own in-
sample and out-of-sample buckets. Keep several per setup
to test different periods or rule tweaks side by side. And
the All tab simply pools everything you've toggled on into
one combined view.

7
00:01:29.976 --> 00:01:36.480
Build your edge in-sample. Prove it out-of-sample. And
never trade a rule you haven't tested on data it has never
seen.
